  "text": "Modulation of IFN by endocytosis, signaling, and TLR inhibitors. Freshly isolated pDCs were incubated with 20 μM methyl-β-cyclodextrin (MβCD) (Sigma-Aldrich), 1 hour at 37°C, clathrin-mediated endocytosis inhibitor, the dynamin inhibitor Dynasore 80 μM (Abcam); 1 μM of IKKβ inhibitor, which inhibits NF-κB signaling, PF184 (Torcis); or 1 μM of MAPK p38 inhibitor SB203580 (Cell Signaling Technology). TLR7 and TLR9 inhibitors have been previously described and were synthesized by IDT [CITATION_1] . Virus with and without HIV Ab was then added to the pDCs and IFN-α production measured after 15 hours. jci.org",
